        "timestamp": "2017-08-03 04:30:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI have in mind to change run.sh script[1], because it was designed to have user interaction.  The unit_testing.sh script is called by vagrant[2], so there is no way to pass arguments besides TEST_SUITE and TEST_CASE environment values\n\n[1] https://git.onap.org/integration/tree/bootstrap/vagrant-onap/tools/run.sh#n13\n[2] https://git.onap.org/integration/tree/bootstrap/vagrant-onap/Vagrantfile#n368",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "935bb586ec078010c67468e0b16b2ef13a46dbdf",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 299,
          "name": "Nate Potter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Nathaniel.Potter@intel.com",
          "username": "ntpttr"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-03 18:11:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHi Victor - that makes sense, though I think if the unit_testing file is intende to be called only by Vagrant maybe we should put it in a folder called vagrant_utils or something. It's a little confusing having it in the main directory, it seems like it should be called by the user to perform unit tests.\n\nI'll update this patch to remote the unneeded instructions rather than adding options.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "00ba761eede46de8bb90633a40fe198f7858dbf8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 947,
          "name": "Victor Morales",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "chipahuac@hotmail.com",
          "username": "electrocucaracha"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-08 01:32:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Hi Victor - that makes sense, though I think if the unit_testing\n > file is intende to be called only by Vagrant maybe we should put it\n > in a folder called vagrant_utils or something. It's a little\n > confusing having it in the main directory, it seems like it should\n > be called by the user to perform unit tests.\n > \n > I'll update this patch to remote the unneeded instructions rather\n > than adding options.\n\n+1, unit_testing.sh and postinstall.sh are scripts used for shell provisioning so if you decided to create a folder just remember to move both and update the references in Vagrantfile",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
